Detailed Description

Obit type definition file.

This defines various enumerations and types to be used in Obit.

enum obitInfoType
 

enum for ObitInfoElem element data types.

For integers use OBIT_long

Enumeration values:
OBIT_byte  8-bit signed byte
OBIT_short  16 bit signed integer
OBIT_int  signed integer
OBIT_oint  Equivalent of FORTRAN INTEGER.
OBIT_long  32 bit signed integer
OBIT_ubyte  8-bit unsigned byte
OBIT_ushort  16 bit unsigned integer
OBIT_uint  unsigned integer
OBIT_ulong  32 bit unsigned signed integer
OBIT_float  single precision float
OBIT_double  double precision float
OBIT_complex  single precision complex
OBIT_dcomplex  double precision complex
OBIT_string  character
OBIT_bool  boolean
OBIT_bits  Bit array packed into gints.

enum obitIOAccess
 

enum for I/O access type.

This specifies Read or read/write access

Enumeration values:
OBIT_IO_None  None (closed).
OBIT_IO_ReadOnly  Read Only.
OBIT_IO_ReadCal  Read with selection, calibration, editing (UV data only).
OBIT_IO_WriteOnly  Write only.
OBIT_IO_ReadWrite  Read and/or write.

enum obitIOCode
 

enum for I/O return codes.

Enumeration values:
OBIT_IO_OK  OK.
OBIT_IO_EOF  Hit end of file - all higher values represent real errors.
OBIT_IO_SpecErr  Specification error.
OBIT_IO_OpenErr  Open error.
OBIT_IO_CloseErr  Close error.
OBIT_IO_ReadErr  Read Error.
OBIT_IO_WriteErr  Write Error.
OBIT_IO_DeleteErr  Delete error.
OBIT_IO_NotFoundErr  Item not found error.

enum obitIOSize
 

enum for I/O data transfer size This specifies Read or read/write access

Enumeration values:
OBIT_IO_byRow  Transfer by image row.
OBIT_IO_byPlane  Transfer by image plane.

enum obitIOStatus
 

enum for object status.

This specifies the status of the connection a disk resident data.

Enumeration values:
OBIT_Inactive  Unconnected to disk resident data, no information defined.
OBIT_Defined  Descriptor created but not connected to a disk file(s).
OBIT_Active  Fully defined and connected to disk resident structures.
OBIT_Modified  Fully defined and I/O active, buffers modified.
OBIT_ErrorExist  An error has been encountered.

enum obitIOType
 

enum for I/O file type.

This specifies the type of underlying data file.

Enumeration values:
OBIT_IO_FITS  FITS.
OBIT_IO_AIPS  AIPS.
OBIT_IO_MEM  Memory only.
OBIT_IO_Binary  Binary data.
OBIT_IO_Text  Text file.
